xture then leave to cool. Discard steaming water."},{"content":"Place garlic in mixing bowl then grate <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>."},{"content":"Add avocados, vinegar, 2 Tbsp oil, salt and pepper then blend <b>4 sec\/speed 10<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then blend again <b>6 sec\/speed 10<b>."},{"content":"Once quinoa is cool, place a sheet of nori, shiny side down onto a bamboo sushi mat then gently spread 6 Tbsp prepared quinoa over nori sheet with a wet, soft spatula (see tip), leaving ⅓ clear at the far end. Spread 1 heaped Tbsp avocado cream in a line across quinoa at the end closest to you, then layer 4 strips of baked sweet potato and 4 sticks of red pepper on avocado cream. Using bamboo sushi mat, begin rolling tightly to form a roll. Before reaching the other end brush edge with vinegar-water mixture (see tip) to help seal, then continue rolling tightly. Set finished roll aside then continue assembling remaining rolls."},{"content":"Slice each roll into 1.5 cm pieces using a wet, sharp knife, wiping clean between each slice. Serve with soy sauce for dipping."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Many people think sushi means raw fish, but it is actually a reference to vinegared rice combined with various ingredients. Here. we've used quinoa instead of rice to create a plant based vegan sushi option packed with nutrients.","Place <b>200 g<b> water and <b>2 Tbsp<b> rice vinegar in a bowl to use for brushing and keeping hands and utensils wet so they don't stick to quinoa.","For optimum quality, sushi is best served immediately or within a few hours of making. Wrap rolls in cling film and leave in a cool dry place then slice just before serving.","Sushi can be wrapped in cling film and refrigerated. Consume within <b>24 hours<b> and be mindful that the quality decreases quickly due to the quinoa losing moisture."],"basicInfo":["medium","45m","1h 30m","72 pieces"]}